WEBVTT

00:06.005 --> 00:09.350
Look, Claud, he probably just decided to
stay a couple extra days in Scottsdale.

00:09.592 --> 00:11.487
You know, to sightsee
or something.

00:11.511 --> 00:13.322
Anyway, are you sure
he even said Saturday?

00:13.346 --> 00:14.281
I don't remember that.

00:14.305 --> 00:15.440
Yes.

00:15.598 --> 00:17.201
'Cause when we went to
the nursery last week,

00:17.225 --> 00:18.828
they said that we could
come back Saturday

00:18.852 --> 00:20.037
and pick up all the seeds

00:20.061 --> 00:21.872
and plants that we would
need for the garden.

00:21.896 --> 00:23.582
And Grandpa said
that would be great,

00:23.606 --> 00:25.658
because that was the day
that he was coming home.

00:25.734 --> 00:28.578
Come to think of it, we were gonna
watch that fight on the pay-per-view.

00:29.154 --> 00:30.589
He said he had a
couple of bucks on it.

00:30.613 --> 00:33.666
Look, I know... I know you guys
probably don't wanna to hear this,

00:33.783 --> 00:36.377
but I think we should be
open to the possibility...

00:37.203 --> 00:38.755
That maybe this is it.

00:39.456 --> 00:40.590
For us.

00:41.916 --> 00:44.844
You know, maybe he just...
Split.

00:45.003 --> 00:46.105
No way.

00:46.129 --> 00:47.189
What do you mean split?

00:47.213 --> 00:48.765
I mean, he's had enough.

00:49.174 --> 00:51.059
And he's gone. Possibly.

00:51.676 --> 00:53.019
He's done it before.

00:53.178 --> 00:54.488
And think about it,

00:54.512 --> 00:56.898
we don't have a telephone
number where we can call him.

00:57.307 --> 01:00.443
When he goes away, he never
leaves us a phone number, right?

01:00.727 --> 01:02.747
And he said he was gonna
be back two days ago,

01:02.771 --> 01:04.415
and he's still not back. So...

01:04.438 --> 01:06.491
You really think we might
not see him again?

01:07.692 --> 01:09.660
I just have this weird feeling.
What if you're right?

01:11.237 --> 01:13.081
You guys, his stuff
is still here.

01:13.656 --> 01:14.791
So what?

01:15.533 --> 01:17.460
Do you think he... Do
you think he, like...

01:17.952 --> 01:19.972
Like, packed when he left Mom?

01:19.996 --> 01:22.725
No. He didn't. He just... He
took whatever he had with him,

01:22.749 --> 01:24.342
he got in his car,
and that was that.

01:25.877 --> 01:27.011
No.

01:27.212 --> 01:28.481
No, no, no. You're wrong.

01:28.505 --> 01:29.774
Something horrible happened.

01:29.798 --> 01:32.943
He, like... He, like, forgot his blood
pressure medication or something.

01:32.967 --> 01:34.445
Hey, calm down.
What are you doing?

01:34.469 --> 01:36.155
Um, can you please give
me all the numbers

01:36.179 --> 01:37.980
to all the hospitals in Arizona?

01:38.223 --> 01:39.357
Claudia.

01:40.266 --> 01:41.776
He wouldn't just leave.

01:42.685 --> 01:44.153
I know he wouldn't.

01:51.361 --> 01:54.465
<i>♪ Everybody wants to live ♪</i>

01:54.489 --> 01:56.092
<i>♪ Like they wanna live ♪</i>

01:56.116 --> 01:59.512
<i>♪ And everybody wants to love ♪</i>

01:59.536 --> 02:01.222
<i>♪ Like they wanna love ♪</i>

02:01.246 --> 02:04.799
<i>♪ Everybody wants to be ♪</i>

02:04.874 --> 02:09.762
<i>♪ Closer to free ♪</i>

02:09.795 --> 02:12.849
<i>♪ Closer to free ♪</i>

02:18.596 --> 02:21.441
<i>Good morning, San
Francisco, I'm Mark...</i>

02:21.641 --> 02:23.077
Where's that dry-cleaning slip?

02:23.101 --> 02:25.204
I have this skimpy black
thing that's perfect.

02:25.228 --> 02:26.831
Although I don't wanna
look like a spokesmodel.

02:26.855 --> 02:29.041
I doubled up on wait staff,
and I triple ordered food.

02:29.065 --> 02:31.335
So he should get what he
ordered and get it fast.

02:31.359 --> 02:33.337
I just hope Terrell's not in
another one of his moods.

02:33.361 --> 02:35.047
So, do I write a
speech or don't I?

02:35.071 --> 02:37.498
Think I lost it last year
because I wrote a speech?

02:37.740 --> 02:39.301
Listen to me.

02:39.325 --> 02:41.470
It's the Bay Area
TV News Awards.

02:41.494 --> 02:43.838
They've got a category
for best weather.

02:44.289 --> 02:47.226
I wish I had you next to me to
help me make fun of it all.

02:47.250 --> 02:48.185
Look, Kathleen...

02:48.209 --> 02:49.343
Charlie.

02:53.756 --> 02:55.308
Don't apologize.

02:56.467 --> 02:57.685
You can't be there.

02:58.469 --> 03:00.104
I completely understand.

03:00.638 --> 03:02.825
Well, maybe Terrell
can do it alone.

03:02.849 --> 03:04.285
Now that I've got
everything in place.

03:04.309 --> 03:05.735
Don't be silly.

03:05.894 --> 03:07.788
You need everything
to be perfect.

03:07.812 --> 03:09.655
Critics only give
you one chance.

03:10.481 --> 03:11.782
You're not angry at me?

03:12.901 --> 03:15.870
You don't have to be
so careful, Charlie.

03:17.238 --> 03:18.915
I mean, I'm disappointed...

03:20.700 --> 03:22.084
But I do understand.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.629
'Cause I don't want you
thinking that I'm not trying.

03:26.164 --> 03:27.423
You've been great.

03:28.374 --> 03:30.426
So relax, okay?

03:36.216 --> 03:38.476
But, if you want extra credit,

03:39.552 --> 03:41.562
you could help me
pick an outfit.

03:48.019 --> 03:48.913
Grandpa?

03:48.937 --> 03:50.279
That would be me.

03:50.688 --> 03:52.573
- Boy, you're back.
- Yeah.

03:54.651 --> 03:55.993
Do you know what today is?

03:57.403 --> 03:58.756
Hello to you too, Bailey.

03:58.780 --> 04:00.831
You were supposed to be
back here three days ago.

04:01.032 --> 04:04.178
We called, like, 50 hospitals
in Scottsdale last night.

04:04.202 --> 04:06.972
They don't have 50
hospitals in Scottsdale.

04:06.996 --> 04:08.224
Claudia had nightmares.

04:08.248 --> 04:10.017
Just that one, Bay.

04:10.041 --> 04:12.228
Well, I didn't mean to
cause a riot or anything.

04:12.252 --> 04:14.929
It's just... My
meetings ran long.

04:15.880 --> 04:17.065
Did I miss something?

04:17.089 --> 04:19.485
Well, I picked up all the
stuff for the gardening.

04:19.509 --> 04:20.402
It's all in the shed.

04:20.426 --> 04:21.695
That reminds me.

04:21.719 --> 04:23.688
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute. That's it?

04:24.347 --> 04:25.481
Now, this...

04:26.182 --> 04:28.285
Will keep your head
from baking in the sun.

04:28.309 --> 04:29.203
Oh, thanks.

04:29.227 --> 04:32.081
Hey, you should have called. "Hello,
I'm gonna be a few days late."

04:32.105 --> 04:34.792
What... What is so
difficult with that? Huh?

04:34.816 --> 04:37.086
Look, this... This is not a
bed-and-breakfast here. Okay?

04:37.110 --> 04:40.256
If you're gonna be, like,
gone, we're gonna notice.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.091
And we're gonna... We're gonna
worry and we're gonna think...

04:42.115 --> 04:45.084
Bailey, he said he was sorry,
and he's here. So just...

04:45.285 --> 04:46.711
Shut up already.

04:47.036 --> 04:49.880
I guess I'm not used to
anybody expecting me.

04:52.125 --> 04:53.426
But, uh, sorry.

04:54.919 --> 04:59.932
It won't happen again.
Okay? Bailey?

05:04.887 --> 05:06.022
Okay.

05:11.477 --> 05:12.987
So which is it gonna be?

05:13.521 --> 05:16.417
Gonna take the test like every
other bookworm, or you gonna...

05:16.441 --> 05:18.701
Get creative and
take option "B"?

05:18.818 --> 05:20.713
I'm just gonna take
the test, Justin.

05:20.737 --> 05:23.247
I don't have time to write
a whole folk tale thing.

05:24.615 --> 05:26.751
Well, we could do it together.

05:26.993 --> 05:28.461
It could be kind of fun.

05:28.786 --> 05:30.556
We could cook up
some crazy story

05:30.580 --> 05:32.474
about star-crossed
lovers on the run.

05:32.498 --> 05:35.051
I'd rather just take the test.
Get it over with, okay?

05:36.169 --> 05:38.814
You know, these stickers, I
never would have put 'em on

05:38.838 --> 05:40.399
if I'd known I'd have to
live with them for, like,

05:40.423 --> 05:42.266
the rest of my time
on the planet.

05:44.177 --> 05:47.188
<i>Once, there was a
couple named...</i>

05:47.805 --> 05:50.691
<i>Named Jersey and Geraldine.</i>

05:51.476 --> 05:53.078
<i>They'd been together so long,</i>

05:53.102 --> 05:55.946
<i>they could barely remember
a time when they weren't.</i>

05:56.439 --> 05:58.792
<i>But they remember the
moment they fell in love,</i>

05:58.816 --> 06:01.128
<i>because even though it
was a long time ago,</i>

06:01.152 --> 06:03.162
<i>it felt like yesterday to them.</i>

06:04.113 --> 06:06.467
<i>Or at least yesterday
it felt like yesterday</i>

06:06.491 --> 06:09.543
<i>because today they had
started to drift apart.</i>

06:10.203 --> 06:11.712
You know what it is, I just...

06:12.497 --> 06:14.224
I hate this room.

06:14.248 --> 06:17.061
It's all the same stuff. The...
The flowered rug,

06:17.085 --> 06:20.262
the little jewelry house,
the dried flowers,

06:20.713 --> 06:22.816
stupid animal stickers...

06:22.840 --> 06:26.769
<i>And Geraldine knew it was
all their house's fault.</i>

06:27.220 --> 06:29.698
<i>Because the old place
was full of problems,</i>

06:29.722 --> 06:33.025
<i>like the cracks that let in
the cold air in the winter</i>

06:33.184 --> 06:35.778
<i>and pipes that were so squeaky,</i>

06:35.895 --> 06:39.240
<i>they played the "Twilight
Zone Theme" every night.</i>

06:39.690 --> 06:42.618
<i>So they decided it was
time to move away.</i>

06:45.863 --> 06:49.218
Did you know that, uh, your
great-grandfather had a farm?

06:49.242 --> 06:52.336
And on his farm he had some ducks.
Right-o?

06:56.916 --> 06:58.050
Hey, Bay.

06:58.501 --> 06:59.677
Come on, dig in.

07:00.545 --> 07:02.815
I think your brother's
still mad at me.

07:02.839 --> 07:05.724
I may have to go to bed
tonight without my supper.

07:05.758 --> 07:07.518
Just come and help us, Bay.

07:09.512 --> 07:11.147
All right. Why not?

07:14.392 --> 07:17.403
Hey. It's kind of fun, huh?

07:18.229 --> 07:20.823
When was the last time we did
a family project out here?

07:21.315 --> 07:22.450
Uh,

07:23.276 --> 07:24.410
Charlie's wedding?

07:24.694 --> 07:27.496
Oh, nice. Nice, nice.
Thank you very much.

07:28.573 --> 07:29.675
Hey.

07:29.699 --> 07:30.592
Oh, I'm sorry.

07:30.616 --> 07:32.668
No, wait a second.
Wait a second.

07:33.119 --> 07:35.171
- How sorry?
- No, don't even think...

07:37.623 --> 07:39.143
Oh! Hey, cut that out!

07:39.167 --> 07:40.509
Ugh!

07:41.627 --> 07:42.729
Back off!

07:42.753 --> 07:43.814
Cut it out!

07:43.838 --> 07:45.691
Claudia! Claudia!

07:45.715 --> 07:47.609
Oh, I dare you.

07:47.633 --> 07:48.735
You dare me?

07:48.759 --> 07:50.686
You dare me?

07:55.183 --> 07:57.077
Uncle! Uncle!

07:57.101 --> 07:59.246
What do you mean "Uncle"?
I'm your grandpa.

07:59.270 --> 08:00.863
You're all confused.

08:01.022 --> 08:02.782
Get back to work now.

08:03.149 --> 08:05.367
That guy's a drill sergeant.
Who knew?

08:08.779 --> 08:10.257
<i>Hi, leave a message</i>

08:10.281 --> 08:12.342
<i>and some Salinger or another
will get back to you. Promise.</i>

08:12.366 --> 08:14.210
<i>Hi, um,</i>

08:14.952 --> 08:16.921
<i>I'm trying to reach Jake Gordon.</i>

08:17.413 --> 08:19.099
<i>Maybe this isn't
the right number.</i>

08:19.123 --> 08:20.591
<i>Uh, I don't know
whose house this is.</i>

08:21.459 --> 08:23.052
<i>If he is here...</i>

08:23.544 --> 08:26.013
<i>Could you tell him that...
That Lauren called?</i>

08:28.132 --> 08:29.558
Hi, sweetheart?

08:31.928 --> 08:35.157
There's room on that top shelf up there.
Can you get me the chair?

08:35.181 --> 08:36.073
Yeah.

08:36.097 --> 08:37.618
<i>so Jersey and Geraldine</i>

08:37.642 --> 08:39.620
<i>started packing away
their old things.</i>

08:39.644 --> 08:40.703
You want me to do it? I can...

08:40.727 --> 08:43.364
No, that's... It's okay.
Just don't let me fall.

08:44.565 --> 08:46.460
<i>There was the head
of the unicorn</i>

08:46.484 --> 08:47.920
<i>he killed to impress her,</i>

08:47.944 --> 08:50.913
<i>not knowing it was her
favorite flying horse,</i>

08:51.656 --> 08:53.342
<i>the broken piece
of looking glass</i>

08:53.366 --> 08:55.219
<i>that she used to put on makeup,</i>

08:55.243 --> 08:57.545
<i>which he said she never needed.</i>

